==English==

===Alternative spellings===
*[[poker faced]]

===Etymology===
From the attitude necessary in the game of [[poker]], since one is ill-advised to reveal delight at being dealt a winning hand lest other players decline to bet (or contrariwise, show disappointment at a poor hand if one is inclined to [[bluff#Verb|bluff]]).

===Adjective===
'''[[poker]]-[[faced]]'''
#Wearing a [[poker face]]: studiously [[neutral]]; giving nothing away.